>>HATSIS: Six-hour rock
concert that this guy

00:32:12.280 --> 00:32:16.240 align:middle line:84%
puts on by himself to
kind of guide people

00:32:16.240 --> 00:32:19.930 align:middle line:84%
through an entheogenic
experience with a backdrop

00:32:19.930 --> 00:32:20.972 align:middle line:90%
of the hero's journey.

00:32:20.972 --> 00:32:22.180 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is it well attended?

00:32:22.180 --> 00:32:23.972 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: It is-- yeah,
it's well attended,

00:32:23.972 --> 00:32:26.380 align:middle line:90%
and it is just remarkable.

00:32:26.380 --> 00:32:29.560 align:middle line:84%
There's also, then, the kind
of weird things that I do,

00:32:29.560 --> 00:32:32.770 align:middle line:84%
because I also use these plant
medicines in my practices.

00:32:32.770 --> 00:32:34.005 align:middle line:90%
I'm a Gaian worshiper.

00:32:34.005 --> 00:32:35.380 align:middle line:84%
Go figure, we're
at Gaia Studios.

00:32:35.380 --> 00:32:37.930 align:middle line:84%
But I actually am a
worshiper of Gaia,

00:32:37.930 --> 00:32:39.280 align:middle line:90%
she who created the universe.

00:32:39.280 --> 00:32:42.460 align:middle line:84%
And I use plant
medicines to be correct--

00:32:42.460 --> 00:32:43.990 align:middle line:90%
direct communication with her.

00:32:43.990 --> 00:32:46.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What has been one
of the strangest experiences

00:32:46.630 --> 00:32:49.900 align:middle line:84%
