the psychedelics?

00:32:49.900 --> 00:32:52.030 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: The strangest.

00:32:52.030 --> 00:32:55.450 align:middle line:84%
After my life, it's kind
of nothing's too strange.

00:32:55.450 --> 00:32:58.900 align:middle line:90%
But let's see.

00:32:58.900 --> 00:33:02.410 align:middle line:84%
A few months ago, when I was
in communication with Gaia,

00:33:02.410 --> 00:33:06.130 align:middle line:84%
she was-- we were talking
about strengths and weaknesses

00:33:06.130 --> 00:33:07.930 align:middle line:90%
in the individual.

00:33:07.930 --> 00:33:10.870 align:middle line:84%
And she was talking
to me about--

00:33:10.870 --> 00:33:13.340 align:middle line:84%
she asked me to grab
this, just, object

00:33:13.340 --> 00:33:14.720 align:middle line:90%
I was sitting on a table.

00:33:14.720 --> 00:33:17.090 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, oh,
well, I'm going for it.

00:33:17.090 --> 00:33:17.890 align:middle line:90%
And she said, no.

00:33:17.890 --> 00:33:18.690 align:middle line:90%
Use your left hand.

00:33:18.690 --> 00:33:20.280 align:middle line:90%
I said, well, I'm right handed.

00:33:20.280 --> 00:33:22.725 align:middle line:84%
Well, one's my
non-dominant hand,

00:33:22.725 --> 00:33:24.100 align:middle line:84%
and the other's
my dominant hand.

00:33:24.100 --> 00:33:25.450 align:middle line:90%
And she said, you're wrong.

00:33:25.450 --> 00:33:27.680 align:middle line:84%
You don't have a
non-dominant hand.

00:33:27.680 --> 00:33:32.110 align:middle line:84%
And then she literally turned
my left arm into a lion's paw.

00:33:32.110 --> 00:33:36.185 align:middle line:84%
So I have a dominant right hand
and a dominant left lion's paw.

00:33:36.185 --> 00:33:37.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:33:37.060 --> 00:33:38.998 align:middle line:90%
What is microdosing?

00:33:38.998 --> 00:33:40.540 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: Microdosing
is the practice

00:33:40.540 --> 00:33:46.270 align:middle line:84%
of taking very small amounts
of things like mushrooms or LSD

00:33:46.270 --> 00:33:49.720 align:middle line:84%
to get the medical
benefits of it,

00:33:49.720 --> 00:33:53.552 align:middle line:84%
which is more energy,
antidepressive effects

00:33:53.552 --> 00:33:54.510 align:middle line:90%
that they have as well.

00:33:54.510 --> 00:33:55.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Anti-anxiety,
that stuff.

00:33:55.930 --> 00:33:57.138 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Anti-anxiety, yeah.

00:33:57.138 --> 00:33:58.690 align:middle line:90%
The list goes on and on.

00:33:58.690 --> 00:34:02.530 align:middle line:84%
And so microdosing is just a
way to take these small amounts

00:34:02.530 --> 00:34:03.815 align:middle line:90%
that are imperceptible.

00:34:03.815 --> 00:34:05.440 align:middle line:84%
When somebody takes
a microdose, you're

00:34:05.440 --> 00:34:07.220 align:middle line:90%
not feeling anything at all.

00:34:07.220 --> 00:34:10.239 align:middle line:84%
It's just working really beneath
the surface and just kind

00:34:10.239 --> 00:34:12.172 align:middle line:90%
of fixing some things.

00:34:12.172 --> 00:34:13.630 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's look
at microdosing.

00:34:13.630 --> 00:34:14.737 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Sure.

00:34:14.737 --> 00:34:15.949 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:34:15.949 --> 00:34:17.850 align:middle line:10%
>>SUE MORTER: is microdosing?

00:34:17.850 --> 00:34:19.850 align:middle line:10%
>>PAUL AUSTIN: So microdosing
is the consumption

00:34:19.850 --> 00:34:23.179 align:middle line:10%
of a low dose of a
psychedelic, usually two times

00:34:23.179 --> 00:34:25.610 align:middle line:10%
per week for a set
period of time,

00:34:25.610 --> 00:34:27.260 align:middle line:10%
like five weeks or 10 weeks.

00:34:27.260 --> 00:34:29.449 align:middle line:10%
When I did it, I did
it for seven months.

00:34:29.449 --> 00:34:32.510 align:middle line:10%
And the idea is that
it's sub-perceptible.

00:34:32.510 --> 00:34:35.960 align:middle line:10%
So you might notice that
there's a slight change in how

00:34:35.960 --> 00:34:39.750 align:middle line:10%
you go about your daily life,
but there's no visual changes.

00:34:39.750 --> 00:34:42.290 align:middle line:10%
You kind of feel like
everything's just a little

00:34:42.290 --> 00:34:46.050 align:middle line:10%
elevated, like everything
sparkles a little bit.

00:34:46.050 --> 00:34:48.139 align:middle line:10%
And so basically,
the way microdosing

00:34:48.139 --> 00:34:51.920 align:middle line:10%
came about was in
2012, a guy named

00:34:51.920 --> 00:34:54.560 align:middle line:10%
Dr. Jim Fadiman published a
book called "The Psychedelic

00:34:54.560 --> 00:34:55.909 align:middle line:10%
Explorer's Guide."

00:34:55.909 --> 00:34:57.385 align:middle line:84%
And he included a
chapter in there

00:34:57.385 --> 00:35:00.140 align:middle line:84%
on microdosing that talked
about the experiences

00:35:00.140 --> 00:35:01.850 align:middle line:84%
that people had
with microdosing,

00:35:01.850 --> 00:35:04.010 align:middle line:90%
a number of anecdotal reports.

00:35:04.010 --> 00:35:07.880 align:middle line:84%
And then in 2015, he was
on a very popular podcast.

00:35:07.880 --> 00:35:10.970 align:middle line:84%
And that's when it sort of came
out into the cultural sphere,

00:35:10.970 --> 00:35:14.250 align:middle line:84%
and you had everyone in Silicon
Valley, tech executives,

00:35:14.250 --> 00:35:16.280 align:middle line:84%
founders who
started to microdose

00:35:16.280 --> 00:35:20.940 align:middle line:84%
to help with productivity and
creativity, things like that.

00:35:20.940 --> 00:35:22.940 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: how does that
microdose experience

00:35:22.940 --> 00:35:26.930 align:middle line:84%
differ from the high dose
experience for the individual?

00:35:26.930 --> 00:35:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>AUSTIN: So the
best way to explain

00:35:28.430 --> 00:35:31.040 align:middle line:84%
the difference between a
microdose and a high dose

00:35:31.040 --> 00:35:33.840 align:middle line:84%
is with a high dose, it's like
someone is screaming at you.

00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:37.100 align:middle line:84%
They're shaking at you to get
the message of connection,

00:35:37.100 --> 00:35:38.550 align:middle line:90%
of source.

00:35:38.550 --> 00:35:40.550 align:middle line:84%
And that can be very
jarring for people at times

00:35:40.550 --> 00:35:43.070 align:middle line:84%
because it's like a
180 from everyday life.

00:35:43.070 --> 00:35:44.870 align:middle line:84%
Whereas with microdosing,
it's like someone

00:35:44.870 --> 00:35:46.250 align:middle line:90%
is whispering at you.

00:35:46.250 --> 00:35:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And it's soft, and it's calm,
and you can integrate it

00:35:49.490 --> 00:35:51.320 align:middle line:90%
on an ongoing basis.

00:35:51.320 --> 00:35:54.840 align:middle line:84%
I like to compare microdosing
to mindfulness meditation.

00:35:54.840 --> 00:35:56.900 align:middle line:84%
People are noticing
very similar effects

00:35:56.900 --> 00:35:59.635 align:middle line:84%
when they meditate consistently
as when they microdose.

00:35:59.635 --> 00:36:01.010 align:middle line:84%
And so that's
really the best way

00:36:01.010 --> 00:36:04.080 align:middle line:84%
to describe the differences
between the two.

00:36:04.080 --> 00:36:07.490 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And then inside that
microdosing experience,

00:36:07.490 --> 00:36:09.830 align:middle line:84%
what are people
subjectively reporting

00:36:09.830 --> 00:36:12.820 align:middle line:84%
what happens inside
of them for that?

00:36:12.820 --> 00:36:15.380 align:middle line:84%
>>AUSTIN: So the core
thing to pay attention

00:36:15.380 --> 00:36:16.760 align:middle line:84%
to when people
are microdosing is

00:36:16.760 --> 00:36:19.520 align:middle line:84%
they have enhanced
sense of presence.

00:36:19.520 --> 00:36:22.490 align:middle line:84%
So there's less of a
fixation on the past.

00:36:22.490 --> 00:36:25.220 align:middle line:84%
There's less of a fixation
on the future, both of which

00:36:25.220 --> 00:36:27.290 align:middle line:84%
are tied to either
depression in the past

00:36:27.290 --> 00:36:28.950 align:middle line:90%
or anxiety in the future.

00:36:28.950 --> 00:36:31.940 align:middle line:84%
And there's more of an
ability just to be here now,

00:36:31.940 --> 00:36:34.730 align:middle line:84%
to be present with
everything that's going on.

00:36:34.730 --> 00:36:36.230 align:middle line:84%
And again, that's
why so many people

00:36:36.230 --> 00:36:38.870 align:middle line:84%
are microdosing with things
like meditation or yoga,

00:36:38.870 --> 00:36:42.020 align:middle line:84%
because those practices
when combined can really

00:36:42.020 --> 00:36:44.540 align:middle line:84%
help to maintain that
sense of presence.

00:36:44.540 --> 00:36:46.730 align:middle line:84%
Now, when we scope,
kind of zoom outside

00:36:46.730 --> 00:36:49.730 align:middle line:84%
of that, microdosing
people are microdosing

00:36:49.730 --> 00:36:51.050 align:middle line:90%
to help with depression.

00:36:51.050 --> 00:36:53.910 align:middle line:84%
They're microdosing
to help with PTSD.

00:36:53.910 --> 00:36:58.160 align:middle line:10%
They're microdosing to help with
high levels of social anxiety,

00:36:58.160 --> 00:36:58.960 align:middle line:10%
for example.

00:36:58.960 --> 00:37:00.335 align:middle line:10%
And then you also
have people who

00:37:00.335 --> 00:37:02.390 align:middle line:10%
are microdosing to
help with creativity,

00:37:02.390 --> 00:37:05.540 align:middle line:10%
to help with leadership,
to help with productivity.

00:37:05.540 --> 00:37:08.900 align:middle line:10%
And essentially, when
you're microdosing,

00:37:08.900 --> 00:37:10.820 align:middle line:10%
it's just a little
bit easier to access

00:37:10.820 --> 00:37:12.530 align:middle line:10%
what we call a flow state.

00:37:12.530 --> 00:37:15.540 align:middle line:10%
And so kind of a flow state
is when you get in the zone.

00:37:15.540 --> 00:37:18.050 align:middle line:10%
You're able to just drop
into what you're doing

00:37:18.050 --> 00:37:20.060 align:middle line:10%
and just to be there with
it and to go into it.

00:37:20.060 --> 00:37:23.720 align:middle line:10%
And that's when creativity
and productivity combine,

00:37:23.720 --> 00:37:25.880 align:middle line:10%
and we're able to really
focus on the project

00:37:25.880 --> 00:37:28.530 align:middle line:10%
at hand to be able to do
it as well as possible.

00:37:28.530 --> 00:37:29.330 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:37:29.330 --> 00:37:31.247 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's Paul
Austin, a friend of yours

00:37:31.247 --> 00:37:34.470 align:middle line:84%
who talks very similarly
to what you've been saying.

00:37:34.470 --> 00:37:35.910 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Yeah, yeah.

00:37:35.910 --> 00:37:39.030 align:middle line:84%
He's really been the
champion of microdosing.

00:37:39.030 --> 00:37:42.570 align:middle line:84%
I would say that he
mentioned Paul Fadiman.

00:37:42.570 --> 00:37:44.160 align:middle line:90%
Paul Fadiman threw that ball.

00:37:44.160 --> 00:37:45.690 align:middle line:84%
Paul Austin caught
it, and he's been

00:37:45.690 --> 00:37:47.040 align:middle line:90%
running with it ever since.

00:37:47.040 --> 00:37:48.498 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tom, why
does there appear

00:37:48.498 --> 00:37:53.430 align:middle line:84%
to be a taboo that
encompasses psychedelics?

00:37:53.430 --> 00:37:55.680 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: Mostly--
and I hope I don't

00:37:55.680 --> 00:37:57.990 align:middle line:84%
upset too many of your
viewers when I say this--

00:37:57.990 --> 00:38:01.020 align:middle line:84%
but mostly, it has
to do with the 1960s.

00:38:01.020 --> 00:38:05.340 align:middle line:84%
The 1960s was actually the only
time in all of human history

00:38:05.340 --> 00:38:08.840 align:middle line:84%
that these medicines were
not revered for the medicines

00:38:08.840 --> 00:38:09.640 align:middle line:90%
that they are.

00:38:09.640 --> 00:38:13.890 align:middle line:84%
And people weren't using them
in reverential, spiritual

00:38:13.890 --> 00:38:15.810 align:middle line:90%
contexts.

00:38:15.810 --> 00:38:18.840 align:middle line:84%
They weren't trying to get
in touch with Gaia or Jesus,

00:38:18.840 --> 00:38:19.800 align:middle line:90%
if that's your thing.

00:38:19.800 --> 00:38:22.215 align:middle line:84%
They were using it as a
party drug and realizing--

00:38:22.215 --> 00:38:23.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: To get high.

00:38:23.090 --> 00:38:24.257 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Yeah, to get high.

00:38:24.257 --> 00:38:28.020 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, acid,
LSD, that's not beer.

00:38:28.020 --> 00:38:32.430 align:middle line:84%
And if you think you can just go
to a house party and take acid

00:38:32.430 --> 00:38:35.820 align:middle line:84%
the way you'd fill
up a beer at a keg--

00:38:35.820 --> 00:38:38.260 align:middle line:84%
and people are having
really bad reactions.

00:38:38.260 --> 00:38:39.060 align:middle line:90%
It's endangering.

00:38:39.060 --> 00:38:40.920 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: These are jumping
out of buildings sometimes,

00:38:40.920 --> 00:38:41.922 align:middle line:90%
in some cases.

00:38:41.922 --> 00:38:43.407 align:middle line:90%
That happened.

00:38:43.407 --> 00:38:45.990 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: Only Ralph Metzner did
that, from what I understand.

00:38:45.990 --> 00:38:47.280 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The CIA guy, right?

00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:48.210 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: Oh no,
that was Frank Olson.

00:38:48.210 --> 00:38:49.335 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You remember that?

00:38:49.335 --> 00:38:51.000 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: He was
pushed out, I think.

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:52.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm one of those guys.

00:38:52.020 --> 00:38:55.260 align:middle line:84%
I think Frank Olson was
pushed out of that window.

00:38:55.260 --> 00:38:57.590 align:middle line:84%
But so unfortunately,
what happened

00:38:57.590 --> 00:38:58.600 align:middle line:90%
is you have mass media.

00:38:58.600 --> 00:39:02.380 align:middle line:84%
You also had the mass
production of television.

00:39:02.380 --> 00:39:08.790 align:middle line:84%
So what happened was
America's first real look

00:39:08.790 --> 00:39:12.630 align:middle line:84%
at these substances, at
these plant medicines,

00:39:12.630 --> 00:39:17.070 align:middle line:84%
was in a highly biased media
controlled kind of way.

00:39:17.070 --> 00:39:20.970 align:middle line:84%
And everybody today-- Paul
Austin, myself, Martin Ball,

00:39:20.970 --> 00:39:22.350 align:middle line:90%
who you've interviewed as well--

00:39:22.350 --> 00:39:25.650 align:middle line:84%
we're all working
double time to try

00:39:25.650 --> 00:39:29.220 align:middle line:84%
to show that, no, these
are actually really--

00:39:29.220 --> 00:39:31.830 align:middle line:84%
I think mystical experiences
are good for people.

00:39:31.830 --> 00:39:32.678 align:middle line:90%
I think they are.

00:39:32.678 --> 00:39:35.220 align:middle line:84%
And I think that you're missing
out if you're not having one.

00:39:35.220 --> 00:39:37.740 align:middle line:84%
And I don't even mean just
by using psychedelics.

00:39:37.740 --> 00:39:39.450 align:middle line:90%
I mean just having--

00:39:39.450 --> 00:39:41.370 align:middle line:84%
a naturally occurring
mystical appearance

00:39:41.370 --> 00:39:42.600 align:middle line:90%
is great for a person.

00:39:42.600 --> 00:39:44.820 align:middle line:84%
But all of that mysticism
and that ideology

00:39:44.820 --> 00:39:46.740 align:middle line:90%
got wrapped up in psychedelia.

00:39:46.740 --> 00:39:49.260 align:middle line:84%
So then people looked at
even that kind of stuff

00:39:49.260 --> 00:39:50.970 align:middle line:84%
like, oh, that's
woo woo or whatever.

00:39:50.970 --> 00:39:53.130 align:middle line:84%
And it's like no, there's
actually a lot to it.

00:39:53.130 --> 00:39:54.797 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you
recommend that people

00:39:54.797 --> 00:39:58.963 align:middle line:84%
get in touch with that outside
world through psychedelics?

00:39:58.963 --> 00:40:01.380 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: I don't recommend
anybody ever take psychedelics

00:40:01.380 --> 00:40:01.770 align:middle line:90%
at all.

00:40:01.770 --> 00:40:02.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You do not.

00:40:02.620 --> 00:40:04.350 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: No.

00:40:04.350 --> 00:40:08.490 align:middle line:84%
But if you're going to, yes,
try to have a reverential

00:40:08.490 --> 00:40:09.550 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:40:09.550 --> 00:40:11.970 align:middle line:84%
I say prayers
before I take mine.

00:40:11.970 --> 00:40:13.770 align:middle line:90%
There's incense that I light.

00:40:13.770 --> 00:40:17.910 align:middle line:84%
It's a whole thing that I do
before I eat my mushrooms.

00:40:17.910 --> 00:40:22.320 align:middle line:84%
But I think that they're--
as long as people know what

00:40:22.320 --> 00:40:24.690 align:middle line:84%
they're doing, they're
educated on the topic,

00:40:24.690 --> 00:40:27.510 align:middle line:84%
they don't have a history
of mental illness either

00:40:27.510 --> 00:40:32.220 align:middle line:84%
in themselves or their family,
they have a friend that's right

00:40:32.220 --> 00:40:34.680 align:middle line:84%
there with them that can
help, that perhaps has had

00:40:34.680 --> 00:40:36.900 align:middle line:90%
experiences before--

00:40:36.900 --> 00:40:38.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm just trying to
keep us out of trouble

00:40:38.760 --> 00:40:41.080 align:middle line:90%
by saying no, don't eat any.

00:40:41.080 --> 00:40:43.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And what about a
person who's got schizophrenia?

00:40:43.560 --> 00:40:44.790 align:middle line:90%
Should he use these?

00:40:44.790 --> 00:40:46.180 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: I don't think so.

00:40:46.180 --> 00:40:47.210 align:middle line:90%
I don't think so at all.

00:40:47.210 --> 00:40:48.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's good advice.

00:40:48.930 --> 00:40:55.650 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: I think even somebody
with mild schizophrenia or--

00:40:55.650 --> 00:40:57.840 align:middle line:84%
it's one of those, talk
to your doctor about it.

00:40:57.840 --> 00:41:00.520 align:middle line:84%
See, that's one of the problems
with all the restrictions in--

00:41:00.520 --> 00:41:03.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Hey doc, I want to eat
these psychedelic mushrooms.

00:41:03.690 --> 00:41:05.245 align:middle line:90%
But a doctor will say no.

00:41:05.245 --> 00:41:06.120 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Not always.

00:41:06.120 --> 00:41:06.920 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:41:06.920 --> 00:41:08.940 align:middle line:84%
>>HATSIS: There's a
whole underground world

00:41:08.940 --> 00:41:12.780 align:middle line:84%
of doctors out in America
and Canada and Mexico that--

00:41:12.780 --> 00:41:15.990 align:middle line:84%
and in Europe, all over
the place-- that are,

00:41:15.990 --> 00:41:17.770 align:middle line:84%
they're psychedelic
psychotherapists.

00:41:17.770 --> 00:41:18.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's
your website, Tom,

00:41:18.720 --> 00:41:21.180 align:middle line:84%
for people who might want
to track you and follow you?

00:41:21.180 --> 00:41:21.980 align:middle line:90%
>>HATSIS: Sure.

